ing title and writing to the database).\n- Chain the actions sequentially within the coroutine:\n    1. Extract URL from intent.\n    2. Launch a coroutine in a persistent scope.\n    3. Fetch the page title (e.g., using Jsoup).\n    4. Save the new bookmark to the Room database.\n    5. On completion, switch back to the main thread to show the \"Bookmark added\" toast.\n    6. Call `finish()` on the activity.\n- All related logic in `MainActivity` has been removed to avoid redundancy.\n\nEXECUTION STATE:\n- The investigation phase is complete.\n- `ShareReceiverActivity.kt` has been identified and read.\n- Redundant logic in `MainActivity.kt` was identified and removed.\n- `AndroidManifest.xml` was modified to correctly route intents.\n- A transparent theme has been applied to `ShareReceiverActivity`.\n- The `Jsoup` dependency has been added to `app/build.gradle.kts`.\n- The implementation of the fix in `ShareReceiverActivity.kt` is the main pending task, focusing on the coroutine scope and `finish()` call timing.\n\nPENDING CHECKS:\n- None. The problem is well-understood, and the path to the solution is clear. The next step is implementation.\n\nAVOID REGRESSION:\n- Do not re-introduce share handling logic into `MainActivity`.\n- Do not use a `CoroutineScope` tied to the `Activity`'s lifecycle (like `lifecycleScope` or `viewModelScope`) for the save operation, as the activity is designed to be short-lived.\n- Do not call `finish()` before the database write and toast display are guaranteed to have been dispatched.\n\nIMPORTANT ERRORS / POLICY EVENTS:\n- None. The previous steps were about analysis and cleanup, which were successful.\n\nEXECUTION SNAPSHOT\ntask_kind=HYBRID\nprotected_working_material=0\ndo_not_reread_without_reason=true\n\nContinue the current task normally. Do not answer with a summary unless the user explicitly asks for one."
